DataElement.preferredName: Practice-Based Research Collaborative in Evidence-Based  Dentistry Dentist Identifier Number
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Number consisting of one or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of an individual licensed for the prevention, diagnosis, and treatment of diseases in the oral cavity, adjacent tissues, and related structures within a network of dental practices that will establish the  infrastructure to perform a wide variety of oral health research studies  in Idaho, Montana, Oregon, Utah and Washington.
